OL,7,F"The company would have irrevocably
OL,8,Fand unilaterally closed down primary
OL,9,Fsteelmaking at British Steel," Mr
OL,10,FReynolds said during the debate. "We
OL,11,Fcould not, will not and never will
OL,12,Fstand idly by while heat seeps from
OL,13,Fthe UK's remaining blast furnaces
OL,14,Fwithout any planning, any due process
OL,15,For any respect for the consequences."
OL,17,FHe explained that the decision to
OL,18,Frecall parliament was not made
OL,19,F"lightly", but that the debate was
OL,20,F"needed."
